(141, 214, 117, 1, '2014-03-03', '2014-08-29', 'The internship’s objective was to build an assessment method merging human factors and flight tests regarding the Elbit Skylens system. This system, easy to install and retrofit, is a “Near To Eyes” devices or NTE. An NTE is simply a virtual collimated display with the projection lenses placed in front of one or both of the pilot’s eyes. This type of display is generally mounted on some type of helmet or glasses. This system is used as a Head Up Display (HUD) equipped with Enhance Flight Vision System (EFVS).', NULL, NULL, '2015-04-27 14:26:28', NULL, 'flight-test-engineer-internship', NULL, 'internship', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Flight Test Engineer Internship', NULL),
